               <note>
                  <ab type="description">There are two rivers known by the name ʾAngarab. This
                     record refers to the so called Small ʾAngarab (cfr. <placeName ref="LOC6536Angara">Great ʾAngarab</placeName>) which rises a few miles
                     north of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> and flows southwards
                     to join the <placeName ref="LOC4402Magac">Megeč̣</placeName> river, which in
                     turn empties into the Lake <placeName ref="LOC5888Tana">Ṭānā</placeName>. The
                     Small ʾAngarab and the <placeName ref="LOC5148Qaha">Qāhā</placeName> river
                     skirt the western and eastern sides of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> respectively. They are the main sources of water of the
                     city and they join south of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>
                     near <placeName ref="LOC2999EslamB">ʾƎslām Bet</placeName>, before joining the
                        <placeName ref="LOC4402Magac">Megeč̣</placeName> river.</ab>
               </note>
            </place>
